In this article, President Trump delivers remarks to the Coast Guard at Lake Worth Inlet in Palm Beach, Florida. He expresses his admiration for the Coast Guard and praises their efforts in responding to natural disasters, such as Hurricane Harvey in Texas and Hurricane Irma in Florida. He also mentions their assistance in Puerto Rico. Trump commends the Coast Guard for saving lives and acknowledges the risks they face in dangerous situations. He thanks them on behalf of the country and takes questions from the media. Trump discusses the country's economic progress, including the stock market reaching an all-time high. He emphasizes the importance of a strong military and mentions the investments being made in new equipment. Trump concludes his speech by expressing his pride in the Coast Guard and the special relationship between them and his administration.